            <h3>Major destinations and cultural festivities</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Lapay Bantigue Festival – It is celebrated on September 29 annually during the City’s founding anniversary.</li>
                <li>2. Pagdayao Festival – It is celebrated every June 13 in honor of the City’s patron, Saint Anthony of Padua.</li>
                <li>3. The Masbate City’s Coastal Resource Management Inter- pretive Center (CRMIC) – It is designed to showcase and pro- mote Masbate’s rich coastal environment and heritage. One can plan and begin a journey of discovery and explore the amazing and diverse natural and cultural wonders of the province and its more than 50 islands and islets.</li>
                <li>4. Rodeo Festival – It is celebrated every second Monday of April. It showcases ten competitive rodeo events such as cattle wrestling, lassoing, and bull riding among others.</li>
            </ol>

